%BOM---------------------
Date:5/10/1999 7:25:00 AM
From:jeffbas

" If the stock is weak but the business isn't, that's a good thing, not a bad
thing."

Agree completely. That is the main tenet of value investing. However, it is
very rarely that simple. It is much more often the case that the business is
weak and the challenge is to determine if the stock has
over discounted that or not -- i,e., where is the bottom in the business, or
does the business have some core value which makes it worth more than the
current price no matter where the bottom is.
