%BOM---------------------
Date:5/13/1999 11:46:00 AM
From:Bob Rudd

Jeffrey: I would say the impact of technology in the future would be anything
but off topic for value investors. One of the major negative impacts on value
investing approaches is the potential of tech changes to make toast out of what
had been robust business models. Now you have to ask if a sell off isn't an
indication that a meteor from cyberspace is about to have deep impact on a
previously stable and isolated business ecosystem. We've recently discussed
book stores, greeting cards and encyclopaedia's, but in fact virtually every
business will be impacted by the net and technological changes.
I think we all have to ask, when analyzing whether a business is an oversold
bargain, just what impact current trends and future twists in technology might
have on the basic earning power of the business.
There will certainly be times that the investment community overestimates the
impact of the net and technology on businesses, but it's important to
understand where they're comin from.
Here's another piece in a similar vein:
http://www.forbes.com/karlgaard/
%EOM----------------------

