From:James Clarke

<<"The race isn't always to the swiftest, but that's the way to bet" Damon
Runyon.>>

Depends what the odds are, now, doesn't it? That's what's so elegantly
beautiful about investment analysis. Everybody knows Microsoft is the swiftest
(and everybody may even be right about that) but this is your 4:3 odds horse.
(I might argue a lot of these are 1:2 horses now...even if they win, you
probably still lose money.) What odds is Mike getting on Apple?

I would suggest finding Charlie Munger's comments comparing stock investing to
pari-mutual betting on horses. It got me thinking.

